17 (2) 'Solar power facility' shall have the same meaning as set forth in Code
18 Section 46-3-67.
19 (b) No owner or operator of a solar power facility shall discard or dispose of or cause to
20 be discarded or disposed of a solar panel by placing it in a landfill or other disposal facility;
21 by placing it with other municipal solid waste or commercial solid waste that is or will be
22 delivered to a landfill or other disposal facility; or by any other manner except by delivery
23 to a collection or recovered materials processing facility or other recycling center that
24 accepts solar panels for recycling.
25 (c) Any owner or operator of a solar power facility who violates subsection (b) of this
26 Code section shall be subject to a civil penalty not to exceed $1,000.00 for each offense.
27 The civil penalty provided for in this subsection shall be recoverable in a civil action
28 brought in any court of competent jurisdiction by the Attorney General or any district
29 attorney."
30 SECTION 2.
31 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
